First, we have $\triangle EOA \sim \triangle COB$, so we have \[\frac{EA}{CB}=\frac{OA}{OB}=\frac{3}{3+9}=\frac{1}{4},\] and since we know $CB=9$, we can find that $EA=9/4$.  This means that $DE=9-9/4=27/4$.

